div.p:
The list is one of a number sent by Cooke that are now in the library of the Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne. See notes to M. Cooke to M, 17 January 1885, for a discussion of Cooke's author attributions. The item is a folded folio, giving four pages.
Unless otherwise noted, all entries with an identifying number or letter have an ink ✓ to the left of the numeral or letter. Most have pencil marks adjacent to the left of the entry. Absence of such marks has not been noted: they differ in form and it is not clear whether or not all were made by the same person.
FNI and Index fungorum were accessed 3 September 2021.
The bottom right of the first sheet has been annotated by J. H. Willis: '20 November 1882'.
The list is arranged implicitly in five columns: reference number, Genus, species epithet and author, location, collector (although 'collector' is infrequently stated). The arrangement is formalized in this transcription.
Australian Fungi
